    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "The automatic getters were designed before structs in the ABI were even considered. Especially for arrays, getters as they currently are make sense in certain cases, so I'm a bit reluctant in changing the behaviour altogether. We could change the detail about returning structs once ABIEncoderV2 is the default, though. I would not change it earlier because activating ABIEncoderV2 currently does not silently change the external behaviour of contracts.",
